Detailed Description

Packet Message Containing Peer and Packet information.

We derive from ACE_Data_Block for our packet data. Since these objects will be forwarded to various different thread pools, we have to make sure that the packet object doesn't go out of scope unexpectedly. An ACE_Message_Block will be deleted as soon as it's release() method is called, but the ACE_Data_Blocks it uses are reference counted and only delete when the last reference release()es the block. We use that trait to simplify our object memory management.
